comment: Mirotic (CHI) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Lin (BKN) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Grant (CHI) and Hollis-Jefferson (BKN) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Lopez (CHI) sets the screen on Lin (BKN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Lin (BKN) makes contact to Butler's (CHI) body that affects his jump shot attempt.
Lopez (CHI) sets the screen on Hollis-Jefferson (BKN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Lopez (BKN) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Butler (CHI) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Butler (CHI) makes contact with Hollis-Jefferson (BKN) that affects his SQBR.
Mirotic (CHI) makes contact to Hollis-Jefferson's (BKN) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Lopez (CHI) sets the screen on Hollis-Jefferson (BKN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Detectable with stop watch] Lopez (CHI) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
[Observable in enhanced video] Lopez (BKN) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
Wade (CHI) makes contact to Dinwiddie's (BKN) arms that affects his driving shot attempt.
Wade (CHI) sets the screen on LeVert (BKN) and gives him room to avoid the contact. The two players briefly engage and separate following the screen.
Lopez (CHI) sets the screen on Hollis-Jefferson (BKN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Lopez (BKN) legally contests Butler's (CHI) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Wade (CHI) makes contact with Dinwiddie (BKN) that affects his SQBR.
Lopez (CHI) makes marginal contact with Hollis-Jefferson (BKN) on the screen.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor that Butler (CHI) released his field goal attempt prior to the game clock expiring is confirmed.
